						<summary>

						<p>Slab fixed to the proper right of the entrance into the main shrine (facing east) in the Svayambhuvēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1556 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It is a broken slab. Records the grant of some lands to the god Svayambhudēva by Siṁgapa and Tirumala for the merit of their father Lingarasa of Munimaḍagu.</p>						

						<p>It is dated Śaka 1479 Na[la], Āshādha śu. 12. It corresponds to 1556 A.D., June 19, (Friday).</p>						

						</summary>
